    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-09-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-09-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="316"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d316">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/1530</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 1, 1915</hi>.</date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 5.18 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2730. Your 2038, August 30, and my 2723, 31st.<note n="2" xml:id="d316fn2"
                        >Neither printed.</note> Foreign Office informs me unofficially that as this
                    matter is so closely connected with <pb facs="0489" n="231" xml:id="pg_231"/>
                    whole question of permits for shipping goods of German origin from neutral
                    ports, now under discussion by British Government and about which French
                    Government is also being consulted, they cannot give an answer concerning this
                    point alone but hope to make a statement as to whole matter at a later date.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
